        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:36PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Greenfield Village, or near Taylor, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Taylor, Romulus, Downtown Detroit, Dearborn, Wyandotte, Belle Isle,
Greenfield Village, Westland, Dearborn Heights, Lincoln Park, Allen
Park, Inkster, Melvindale, Ecorse, River Rouge, and Southwest
Detroit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
